Atopica.label: Atopic dermatitis
Atopica.description: Atopic dermatitis is a long-term (chronic) skin disorder that involves scaly and itchy rashes. Other forms of eczema include Contact dermatitis; Dyshidrotic eczema; Nummular eczema; Seborrheic dermatitis.Causes - Symptoms - Tests - Treatment - Prognosis - Prevention National Library of Medicine
